# Docker Workflow

## Core Principle

All commands run inside Docker containers. Never install project dependencies (Flutter SDK, Python, pip packages) directly on the host machine.

## Development

```bash
# Start all services (db, api, app) with hot-reload
docker compose up

# Frontend at http://localhost:5173
# API at http://localhost:8000
```

## Testing

```bash
# Unit tests (Flutter test)
docker compose --profile test run --rm test-unit

# E2E tests (pytest + Playwright)
docker compose --profile test run --rm test-e2e

# Run tests for a specific SRS requirement
docker compose --profile test run --rm test-e2e pytest -m fr1 -v
```

## Database Migrations

```bash
# Generate a new migration after model changes
docker compose exec api alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"

# Apply migrations
docker compose exec api alembic upgrade head
```

## Production Build

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
# Access at http://localhost:80
```

## Key Details

- The `api` service uses a bind-mount for source files so uvicorn reload works
- The `app` service bind-mounts `lib/` and `test/` for Flutter hot-reload
- The `test-e2e` service depends on `app` and `api`, connecting via the Docker network
- Use `docker compose down` to stop all services
- Use `docker compose down -v` to also remove the database volume
